---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ListComponent from "../../components/List.astro";
---

<Layout title="List">
	<div class="container">
		<section class="section">
			<p>The List component creates clean, styled lists with consistent formatting. Perfect for features lists, navigation items, or any structured content that needs clear visual hierarchy.</p>
			
			<h2>Demo</h2>
			<div class="component-demo">
				<h3>Feature List</h3>
				<ListComponent 
					items={[
						"Responsive design that works on all devices",
						"Clean, semantic HTML structure",
						"Accessible markup following WCAG guidelines",
						"Customizable styling with CSS variables",
						"Easy integration with any Astro project"
					]}
				/>

				<h3>Benefits List</h3>
				<ListComponent 
					items={[
						"Improved user experience",
						"Better SEO performance",
						"Faster development time",
						"Consistent visual design",
						"Maintainable code structure"
					]}
				/>

				<h3>Technical Specifications</h3>
				<ListComponent 
					items={[
						"Built with Astro framework",
						"TypeScript support included",
						"SCSS styling architecture",
						"Component-based structure",
						"Zero JavaScript runtime by default"
					]}
				/>
			</div>

			<h3>Features</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Clean, consistent list styling</li>
				<li>Accepts array of strings as items</li>
				<li>Responsive design</li>
				<li>Semantic HTML structure</li>
				<li>Easy to customize with CSS</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Usage Example</h3>
			<pre><code>&lt;ListComponent 
  items={[
    "First item",
    "Second item", 
    "Third item"
  ]}
/&gt;</code></pre>

			<h3>Customization</h3>
			<p>The List component can be easily customized through CSS. You can modify colors, spacing, typography, and add custom icons or styling to match your design system.</p>
		</section>
	</div>
</Layout>